{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Lig3F28vsrfwbzyA5qFHar","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 10.2: Driver Factory & Registry\n2\t\n3\tStatus: verifying\n4\t\n5\t<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n6\t\n7\t## Story\n8\t\n9\tAs a developer,\n10\tI want a driver factory that registers and resolves drivers by name,\n11\tso that the workflow engine can get any driver instance without knowing its implementation class.\n12\t\n13\t## Acceptance Criteria\n14\t\n15\t1. **Given** a new file `src/lib/agents/drivers/factory.ts`\n16\t   **When** inspected\n17\t   **Then** it exports a `registerDriver(driver: AgentDriver): void` function that stores drivers by `driver.name`\n18\t   **And** calling `registerDriver` with a driver whose name is already registered throws an error with the message containing the duplicate name\n19\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n20\t\n21\t2. **Given** the factory module\n22\t   **When** `getDriver('claude-code')` is called after a driver named `'claude-code'` has been registered\n23\t   **Then** it returns the registered `AgentDriver` instance (same reference)\n24\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n25\t\n26\t3. **Given** the factory module\n27\t   **When** `getDriver('unknown')` is called with a name that has no registered driver\n28\t   **Then** it throws an error whose message includes the unknown name and lists all currently registered driver names\n29\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n30\t\n31\t4. **Given** the factory module\n32\t   **When** `listDrivers()` is called\n33\t   **Then** it returns an array of all registered driver names as strings\n34\t   **And** the array is a copy (mutating it does not affect the registry)\n35\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n36\t\n37\t5. **Given** the factory module\n38\t   **When** `resetDrivers()` is called\n39\t   **Then** all registered drivers are cleared\n40\t   **And** subsequent `getDriver()` calls throw, and `listDrivers()` returns an empty array\n41\t   **And** `resetDrivers` is exported (needed for test isolation)\n42\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n43\t\n44\t6. **Given** drivers are registered explicitly via `registerDriver()`\n45\t   **When** the factory module is loaded\n46\t   **Then** there is NO auto-discovery of driver files (no dynamic `import()`, no directory scanning, no glob-based loading)\n47\t   **And** the factory module has no filesystem access at import time\n48\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n49\t\n50\t7. **Given** the barrel file `src/lib/agents/index.ts`\n51\t   **When** inspected\n52\t   **Then** it re-exports `getDriver`, `registerDriver`, `listDrivers`, and `resetDrivers` from `./drivers/factory.js`\n53\t   **And** the old `getDriver()` stub function that throws \"No agent drivers available\" is removed\n54\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n55\t\n56\t8. **Given** the `src/lib/agents/drivers/` directory\n57\t   **When** inspected\n58\t   **Then** it contains at least `factory.ts` and an `index.ts` barrel file\n59\t   **And** the barrel re-exports all public symbols from `factory.ts`\n60\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n61\t\n62\t9. **Given** unit tests in `src/lib/agents/__tests__/factory.test.ts`\n63\t   **When** `npm run test:unit` is executed\n64\t   **Then** tests cover: register and retrieve a driver, retrieve unknown name throws with helpful message, duplicate registration throws, `listDrivers()` returns registered names, `listDrivers()` returns a copy, `resetDrivers()` clears all drivers, factory has no auto-discovery behavior\n65\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n66\t\n67\t10. **Given** `npm run build` is executed\n68\t    **When** the build completes\n69\t    **Then** it succeeds with zero TypeScript errors\n70\t    **And** `npm run test:unit` passes with no regressions in existing test suites\n71\t    <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n72\t\n73\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n74\t\n75\t- [x] Task 1: Create `src/lib/agents/drivers/` directory structure (AC: #8)\n76\t  - [x] Create `src/lib/agents/drivers/factory.ts`\n77\t  - [x] Create `src/lib/agents/drivers/index.ts` barrel file\n78\t\n79\t- [x] Task 2: Implement the driver registry in `factory.ts` (AC: #1, #2, #3, #4, #5, #6)\n80\t  - [x] Implement `registerDriver(driver: AgentDriver): void` — stores by `driver.name`, throws on duplicate\n81\t  - [x] Implement `getDriver(name: string): AgentDriver` — returns instance, throws with helpful error listing all registered names if not found\n82\t  - [x] Implement `listDrivers(): string[]` — returns copy of registered names\n83\t  - [x] Implement `resetDrivers(): void` — clears registry (for test isolation)\n84\t  - [x] Use a plain `Map<string, AgentDriver>` — no dynamic imports, no filesystem scanning\n85\t\n86\t- [x] Task 3: Create `src/lib/agents/drivers/index.ts` barrel (AC: #8)\n87\t  - [x] Re-export `getDriver`, `registerDriver`, `listDrivers`, `resetDrivers` from `./factory.js`\n88\t\n89\t- [x] Task 4: Update `src/lib/agents/index.ts` barrel (AC: #7)\n90\t  - [x] Remove the old `getDriver()` stub function\n91\t  - [x] Re-export `getDriver`, `registerDriver`, `listDrivers`, `resetDrivers` from `./drivers/factory.js`\n92\t\n93\t- [x] Task 5: Write unit tests in `src/lib/agents/__tests__/factory.test.ts` (AC: #9, #10)\n94\t  - [x] Test: register a mock driver and retrieve it by name\n95\t  - [x] Test: `getDriver('nonexistent')` throws with the name and lists registered drivers\n96\t  - [x] Test: duplicate `registerDriver()` throws with the duplicate name\n97\t  - [x] Test: `listDrivers()` returns all registered names\n98\t  - [x] Test: `listDrivers()` returns a copy (push to result does not affect registry)\n99\t  - [x] Test: `resetDrivers()` clears all registrations\n100\t  - [x] Test: factory module source has no `import()`, `readdir`, `glob`, or `require()` calls (grep the file)\n101\t  - [x] Verify `npm run build` passes with zero errors\n102\t  - [x] Verify `npm run test:unit` passes with no regressions\n103\t\n104\t## Dev Notes\n105\t\n106\t### Architecture Compliance\n107\t\n108\tThis story implements the **Driver Factory Pattern** from `_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-multi-framework.md` (Project Structure & Boundaries section). Key constraints:\n109\t\n110\t- **Explicit registration, no auto-discovery** — the architecture mandates \"Register in `factory.ts` — never auto-discover\". Drivers are registered by calling `registerDriver()` at application bootstrap, not by scanning the filesystem.\n111\t- **Factory is a module singleton** — uses module-level `Map`, not a class instance. Import from anywhere, get the same registry.\n112\t- **Factory knows nothing about drivers** — it stores `AgentDriver` instances by name. It does not import `ClaudeCodeDriver`, `CodexDriver`, etc. Those are registered externally (by the bootstrap/entry point, implemented in story 10-5).\n113\t\n114\t### Existing Code to Modify\n115\t\n116\t1. **`src/lib/agents/index.ts`** — Remove the old `getDriver()` stub that throws \"No agent drivers available\". Replace with re-export from `./drivers/factory.js`. The old stub will no longer be needed once the factory is in place.\n117\t\n118\t### What NOT to Do\n119\t\n120\t- Do NOT create driver implementation files (`claude-code.ts`, `codex.ts`, `opencode.ts`) — those are stories 10-3, 12-1, 12-2\n121\t- Do NOT register any drivers in the factory module itself — registration happens at bootstrap (story 10-5)\n122\t- Do NOT import any driver classes in `factory.ts` — it only depends on the `AgentDriver` interface type\n123\t- Do NOT modify `workflow-engine.ts` or `agent-dispatch.ts` — integration comes in story 10-5\n124\t- Do NOT create a `model-resolver.ts` — that is story 10-4\n125\t- Do NOT add filesystem operations (`fs`, `path.glob`, dynamic `import()`) to `factory.ts`\n126\t\n127\t### Dependencies\n128\t\n129\t- **Story 10-1 (done):** `AgentDriver` interface in `src/lib/agents/types.ts` — this story imports the interface type for the registry's type constraint\n130\t- **Stories 10-3, 12-1, 12-2 (future):** Driver implementations that will call `registerDriver()` to register themselves\n131\t- **Story 10-5 (future):** Workflow engine integration that will call `getDriver()` to resolve drivers at dispatch time\n132\t\n133\t### Testing Patterns\n134\t\n135\t- Follow existing Vitest patterns in `src/lib/agents/__tests__/`\n136\t- Create mock `AgentDriver` implementations for testing (minimal objects satisfying the interface)\n137\t- Use `beforeEach(() => resetDrivers())` to ensure test isolation\n138\t- Test the \"no auto-discovery\" AC by grepping `factory.ts` source for forbidden patterns (`import(`, `readdir`, `glob`, `require(`)\n139\t- Use `describe/it/expect` structure consistent with existing test files\n140\t\n141\t### Implementation Notes\n142\t\n143\t- The `Map<string, AgentDriver>` is the entire data structure. No WeakMap, no class, no dependency injection.\n144\t- `getDriver()` error message should be actionable: `\"Driver 'codex' not found. Registered drivers: claude-code, opencode\"` — this helps users debug workflow YAML misconfiguration.\n145\t- `listDrivers()` must return a copy (`[...map.keys()]`) to prevent registry mutation via the returned array.\n146\t\n147\t### References\n148\t\n149\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-multi-framework.md — \"Register in factory.ts — never auto-discover\"]\n150\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-multi-framework.md — Project Structure: `drivers/factory.ts`]\n151\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-multi-framework.md — Story 1.2: Driver Factory & Registry]\n152\t- [Source: src/lib/agents/types.ts — AgentDriver interface (story 10-1)]\n153\t- [Source: src/lib/agents/index.ts — old getDriver() stub to replace]\n154\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_017EZBfbcuBStr9k8HaRFsmc","session_id":"ccf790f5-4b27-4b46-b089-256c4e0022f0","uuid":"830a5bd3-96e4-4cd2-b60b-aa6dfa9e53d7","timestamp":"2026-04-03T06:57:02.419Z"}
