{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01K52AwbduVC4cigJev8MukM","type":"tool_result","content":"114-| Loop iteration counter | TUI shows loop count on loop blocks |\n115-| Output contract passing | Serialize task output to JSON, feed as input to next task across framework boundary |\n116-| Backward compatibility | Workflows without `driver` field default to `claude-code` |\n117:| gstack integration | gstack skills loaded into claude-code driver sessions via config |\n118-| omo integration | omo agents loaded into opencode driver sessions via config |\n119-| Driver capability matrix | Docs showing what each driver can/cannot do |\n120-| Cost-based routing hints | Suggest cheaper driver for simple tasks |\n--\n194-```\n195-Story 1-1 begins. `implement` highlights.\n196-\n197:[Omitted long matching line]\n198-\n199-**Climax:** `verify` highlights — `[codex]`. The Codex driver spawns `codex` CLI with the evaluator's prompt, no source access. The evaluator interacts with the running application, produces a Showboat proof. Three frameworks touched one story. The TUI shows all three nodes as completed with checkmarks, cost per node, and elapsed time.\n200-\n--\n287-\n288-1. **Dogfooding** — Build this feature using codeharness itself. Dev on Claude Code, verify on Codex.\n289-2. **Cross-framework bug catch rate** — Track bugs caught by cross-framework verification that same-framework missed. Target: >15% improvement.\n290:3. **Driver parity test** — Same story implemented via Claude Code driver and Codex driver should produce functionally equivalent results (tests pass on both).\n291-4. **TUI usability** — User can identify current workflow position, active framework, and cost within 3 seconds of glancing at TUI.\n292-\n293-### Innovation Risk Mitigation\n--\n306-- TypeScript driver implementations in `src/lib/agents/drivers/`\n307-- All drivers implement the `AgentDriver` interface: `name`, `spawn()`, `parseOutput()`, `getStatusFile()`\n308-- Drivers bundled in the main `codeharness` npm package — no separate packages\n309:- Claude Code driver uses Agent SDK directly (existing `dispatchAgent()`)\n310-- Codex/OpenCode drivers wrap their CLIs via `child_process.spawn`\n311-- Stream output normalized to common `StreamEvent` protocol per driver\n312-\n--\n328-| claude-code | Agent SDK (in-process) | StreamEvent (native) | Anthropic API key |\n329-| codex | `codex` CLI | stdout NDJSON | OpenAI API key / ChatGPT account |\n330-| opencode | `opencode` CLI | stdout | Per-provider keys |\n331:| gstack | via claude-code driver | StreamEvent (native) | Anthropic API key |\n332-| omo | via opencode driver | stdout | Per-provider keys |\n333-\n334:**Note:** gstack and omo are plugins within their respective frameworks — they don't need separate drivers. gstack skills activate inside Claude Code sessions (claude-code driver), omo agents activate inside OpenCode sessions (opencode driver). The workflow configures which plugins/skills load, not a separate driver.\n335-\n336-### Installation & Distribution\n337-\n--\n396-\n397-### Plugin Ecosystem Integration\n398-\n399:- FR21: User can configure gstack skills to load within claude-code driver sessions via workflow or agent config\n400-- FR22: User can configure omo agents to load within opencode driver sessions via workflow or agent config\n401-- FR23: System can pass plugin-specific configuration to the driver's CLI invocation (e.g., `--plugin`, `--agent` flags)\n402-\n--\n449-\n450-- NFR7: Codex driver must work with Codex CLI versions pinned in package.json — integration tests validate against real CLI output\n451-- NFR8: OpenCode driver must work with OpenCode CLI versions pinned in package.json — integration tests validate against real CLI output\n452:- NFR9: Claude Code driver must maintain compatibility with Agent SDK `@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk` pinned version\n453-- NFR10: Output contract JSON format must be stable across driver versions — contracts written by one driver must be readable by any other\n454-- NFR11: Workflow YAML schema changes must be backward compatible — old workflows work without modification\n455-- NFR12: Plugin ecosystem integration (gstack, omo) must not require modifications to the plugins themselves — configuration only"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_017EZBfbcuBStr9k8HaRFsmc","session_id":"ccf790f5-4b27-4b46-b089-256c4e0022f0","uuid":"deac0b96-3e38-4ecc-92cb-a717d369c773","timestamp":"2026-04-03T06:57:44.513Z"}
