{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014kpGJak6Cg1qrEkzufT4Mi","type":"tool_result","content":"76\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n77\t\n78\t- [ ] Task 1: Create `src/lib/agents/drivers/claude-code.ts` (AC: #1, #4)\n79\t  - [ ] Import `query` from `@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk`\n80\t  - [ ] Import types: `AgentDriver`, `DispatchOpts`, `DriverHealth`, `DriverCapabilities` from `../types.js`\n81\t  - [ ] Import `StreamEvent` types from `../stream-parser.js`\n82\t  - [ ] Implement `ClaudeCodeDriver` class with readonly name, defaultModel, capabilities\n83\t  - [ ] Implement `healthCheck()` returning `{ available: true, authenticated: true, version: null }`\n84\t\n85\t- [ ] Task 2: Implement `dispatch()` method — SDK integration (AC: #2, #3)\n86\t  - [ ] Call `query()` with prompt, model, systemPrompt, cwd, permissionMode from `DispatchOpts`\n87\t  - [ ] Consume the Agent SDK async generator and map messages to `StreamEvent` objects\n88\t  - [ ] Map `content_block_start` (tool_use) to `tool-start` events\n89\t  - [ ] Map `content_block_delta` (input_json_delta) to `tool-input` events\n90\t  - [ ] Map `content_block_delta` (text_delta) to `text` events\n91\t  - [ ] Map `content_block_stop` to `tool-complete` events\n92\t  - [ ] Map system `api_retry` to `retry` events\n93\t  - [ ] Map `result` to final `result` event with cost_usd from `total_cost_usd`\n94\t  - [ ] Store `total_cost_usd` from result message for `getLastCost()`\n95\t  - [ ] Always yield exactly one `result` event at the end\n96\t\n97\t- [ ] Task 3: Implement error classification (AC: #5)\n98\t  - [ ] Extract `classifyError()` as a private method or module function\n99\t  - [ ] Map HTTP 429 or \"rate limit\" in message to `RATE_LIMIT`\n100\t  - [ ] Map ECONNREFUSED, ETIMEDOUT, ENOTFOUND, ENETUNREACH, ECONNRESET, EPIPE to `NETWORK`\n101\t  - [ ] Map HTTP 401/403 or \"unauthorized\"/\"forbidden\" to `AUTH`\n102\t  - [ ] Map timeout kill to `TIMEOUT`\n103\t  - [ ] Default to `UNKNOWN`\n104\t  - [ ] On error, yield a `result` event with error details instead of throwing\n105\t\n106\t- [ ] Task 4: Implement plugin and timeout pass-through (AC: #6, #7)\n107\t  - [ ] When `opts.plugins` is provided, pass to SDK query options\n108\t  - [ ] When `opts.timeout` is provided, implement timeout with `AbortController` or equivalent\n109\t  - [ ] On timeout, abort the SDK generator and yield `result` with TIMEOUT classification\n110\t\n111\t- [ ] Task 5: Update `src/lib/agents/drivers/index.ts` barrel (AC: #8)\n112\t  - [ ] Add `export { ClaudeCodeDriver } from './claude-code.js'`\n113\t  - [ ] Preserve existing factory exports\n114\t\n115\t- [ ] Task 6: Write unit tests (AC: #9, #10)\n116\t  - [ ] Mock `@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk` query function (same pattern as `agent-dispatch.test.ts`)\n117\t  - [ ] Test: dispatch yields correct StreamEvent sequence from mocked SDK messages\n118\t  - [ ] Test: getLastCost() returns cost from last result message\n119\t  - [ ] Test: getLastCost() returns null before any dispatch\n120\t  - [ ] Test: getLastCost() returns null when SDK reports no cost\n121\t  - [ ] Test: healthCheck() returns `{ available: true, authenticated: true, version: null }`\n122\t  - [ ] Test: error classification for RATE_LIMIT (429 status)\n123\t  - [ ] Test: error classification for NETWORK (ECONNREFUSED)\n124\t  - [ ] Test: error classification for AUTH (401 status)\n125\t  - [ ] Test: error classification for TIMEOUT\n126\t  - [ ] Test: error classification for UNKNOWN (default)\n127\t  - [ ] Test: dispatch always yields a result event even when SDK throws\n128\t  - [ ] Test: plugins array passed to SDK options\n129\t  - [ ] Test: no plugins passed when opts.plugins is undefined\n130\t  - [ ] Verify `npm run build` passes with zero errors\n131\t  - [ ] Verify `npm run test:unit` passes with no regressions\n132\t\n133\t## Dev Notes\n134\t\n135\t### Architecture Compliance"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01QaKPQz8Xx3mXJcbS9wN8Y9","session_i