{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QaKPQz8Xx3mXJcbS9wN8Y9","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Story 10-3 is complete. Here is the summary:\n\n**Story:** 10-3 Claude Code Driver Extraction\n**Status:** review\n\n**What was implemented:**\n\n1. **`src/lib/agents/drivers/claude-code.ts`** (new) -- `ClaudeCodeDriver` class implementing `AgentDriver` interface. Uses Agent SDK `query()` in-process. Maps SDK messages to `StreamEvent` objects. Includes `classifyError()` with 5-category classification (RATE_LIMIT, NETWORK, AUTH, TIMEOUT, UNKNOWN). Errors are yielded as result events, never thrown. Plugin pass-through and timeout via `AbortController`.\n\n2. **`src/lib/agents/drivers/index.ts`** (modified) -- Added `ClaudeCodeDriver` export to barrel file, preserving existing factory exports.\n\n3. **`src/lib/agents/__tests__/claude-code-driver.test.ts`** (new) -- 42 tests covering all 10 acceptance criteria: class properties, healthCheck, dispatch event mapping, getLastCost, error classification for all 5 categories, guaranteed result event, plugin pass-through, timeout handling, SDK parameter pass-through, and mid-stream error handling.\n\n**Validation results:**\n- Build: passes (zero TS errors in new files; pre-existing errors in unrelated test files only)\n- New tests: 42/42 passing\n- Full regression suite: 163 files, 4283 tests, all passing\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **Pre-existing TS errors:** `src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts` and `src/commands/__tests__/issue.test.ts` have type errors unrelated to this story. These are pre-existing and do not affect the build (tsup bundles successfully regardless).\n- **ResultEvent error fields:** The `ResultEvent` type from `stream-parser.ts` does not have `error` or `errorCategory` fields. The driver uses type intersection (`ResultEvent & { error: string; errorCategory: ErrorCategory }`) to attach error info. This works at runtime but is a mild type system workaround. A proper `ErrorResultEvent` type could be added in a future story.\n- **DispatchOpts lacks systemPrompt:** The `DispatchOpts` interface does not include a `systemPrompt` field (the story spec mentions it in Task 2 subtask). The driver does not pass `systemPrompt` to the SDK because the interface doesn't have it. This is consistent with the interface design from story 10-1 and the story's \"What NOT to Do\" instructions.\n- **Plugin SDK support:** The story notes say to \"Check SDK types for the correct option shape\" for plugins. The implementation passes `plugins` directly to SDK query options. If the SDK doesn't support this field, it will be silently ignored. This matches the story's guidance to pass via options.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 16\n- By tool: Bash: 5, Read: 8, Edit: 3, Write: 2, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `npm run test:unit` (~500+ lines with ANSI rendering), `npx tsc --noEmit` (~27 lines), `npm run build` (~20 lines)\n- Files read: 9 unique, 9 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: none"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: aeadcabeaa178333c (use SendMessage with to: 'aeadcabeaa178333c' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 76596\ntool_uses: 29\nduration_ms: 236458</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ccf790f5-4b27-4b46-b089-256c4e0022f0","uuid":"63f4f220-7eae-4d39-8ad4-d1abe87ede61","timestamp":"2026-04-03T07:05:15.163Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-dev-story for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/10-3-claude-code-driver-extraction.md — implement all tasks, write tests, and mark the story for review. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously through all tasks until complete. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Problems encountered (build failures, test failures, unclear task sp