{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Verify story 10-3-claude-code-driver-extraction using local CLI checks (test-provable tier).\n\nStory file: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/10-3-claude-code-driver-extraction.md\n\nExecute these steps and report results:\n1. Run the project build command (npm run build). Report: PASS or FAIL + first 10 error lines.\n2. Run tests (npm test). Report: PASS (N passed) or FAIL (N failed: list names).\n3. Run linter if configured (eslint, etc). Report: PASS or FAIL + warning count.\n4. Run coverage if configured (vitest --coverage). Report: coverage percentage.\n5. For each AC in the story file, verify it:\n   - File existence: ls path/to/file\n   - Exports: grep 'export' path/to/file\n   - Function existence: grep 'function name' path/to/file\n   - Test output: check relevant test names in output\n   Report each AC as PASS or FAIL with one-line evidence.\n6. Generate proof document at verification/10-3-claude-code-driver-extraction-proof.md with evidence from each check.\n7. Run codeharness verify --story 10-3-claude-code-driver-extraction to validate the proof format.\n8. Report final result: ALL_PASS (N/N ACs) or PARTIAL (M/N ACs, list failures).\n\nDo NOT ask the user any questions. Do NOT run git commands. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Problems encountered (build failures, test failures, missing files, unexpected behavior)\n- Workarounds applied (anything hacky or suboptimal)\n- Verification gaps (ACs that were hard to verify, weak evidence)\n- Observations (anything surprising or noteworthy)\nIf nothing to report, write `## Session Issues\\n\\nNone.`\n\nMANDATORY — Also end your response with a `## Token Report` section:\n- Total tool calls: N\n- By tool: Bash: X, Read: Y, Edit: Z, Grep: W, Write: V, other: N\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): command (~N lines each)\n- Files read: N unique, M