{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016XSA3xUYmcvaEqdgG8WCH4","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 10.3: Claude Code Driver Extraction\n2\t\n3\tStatus: verifying\n4\t\n5\t<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n6\t\n7\t## Story\n8\t\n9\tAs a developer,\n10\tI want the existing Agent SDK dispatch logic extracted into a ClaudeCodeDriver class,\n11\tso that Claude Code works through the same driver interface as future Codex and OpenCode drivers, and the workflow engine can dispatch uniformly.\n12\t\n13\t## Acceptance Criteria\n14\t\n15\t1. **Given** a new file `src/lib/agents/drivers/claude-code.ts`\n16\t   **When** inspected\n17\t   **Then** it exports a `ClaudeCodeDriver` class that implements the `AgentDriver` interface\n18\t   **And** the class has `readonly name = 'claude-code'`\n19\t   **And** the class has `readonly defaultModel = 'claude-sonnet-4-20250514'`\n20\t   **And** the class has `readonly capabilities` with `{ supportsPlugins: true, supportsStreaming: true, costReporting: true }`\n21\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n22\t\n23\t2. **Given** the `ClaudeCodeDriver.dispatch(opts)` method\n24\t   **When** called with valid `DispatchOpts`\n25\t   **Then** it calls the Agent SDK `query()` function with the prompt, model, cwd, and permission options derived from `opts`\n26\t   **And** it yields `StreamEvent` objects by consuming the Agent SDK async generator and mapping messages to stream events\n27\t   **And** the final event yielded is always a `result` event (even on error)\n28\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n29\t\n30\t3. **Given** the `ClaudeCodeDriver.dispatch(opts)` method\n31\t   **When** the Agent SDK generator yields a `result` message with `total_cost_usd`\n32\t   **Then** the driver captures the cost and `getLastCost()` returns that value\n33\t   **And** if the SDK does not report cost, `getLastCost()` returns `null`\n34\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n35\t\n36\t4. **Given** the `ClaudeCodeDriver.healthCheck()` method\n37\t   **When** called\n38\t   **Then** it returns `{ available: true, authenticated: true, version: null }` (Claude Code Agent SDK is an in-process dependency, always available if the package is installed)\n39\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n40\t\n41\t5. **Given** an error thrown by the Agent SDK during dispatch\n42\t   **When** the error message or properties are inspected\n43\t   **Then** the driver classifies it into the standard `ErrorCategory`: `RATE_LIMIT` (HTTP 429 or \"rate limit\"), `NETWORK` (ECONNREFUSED, ETIMEDOUT, etc.), `AUTH` (HTTP 401/403 or \"unauthorized\"), `TIMEOUT` (process killed by timeout), or `UNKNOWN`\n44\t   **And** the classified error is yielded as a `result` event with the error information, not thrown\n45\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n46\t\n47\t6. **Given** the `ClaudeCodeDriver.dispatch(opts)` method\n48\t   **When** `opts.plugins` contains values (e.g., `['gstack']`)\n49\t   **Then** the driver passes plugin configuration to the Agent SDK query options\n50\t   **And** when `opts.plugins` is undefined or empty, no plugin configuration is passed\n51\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n52\t\n53\t7. **Given** the `ClaudeCodeDriver.dispatch(opts)` method\n54\t   **When** `opts.timeout` is set\n55\t   **Then** the driver applies the timeout to the Agent SDK session\n56\t   **And** if the timeout is exceeded, the driver yields a `result` event with error category `TIMEOUT`\n57\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n58\t\n59\t8. **Given** the barrel file `src/lib/agents/drivers/index.ts`\n60\t   **When** inspected\n61\t   **Then** it re-exports `ClaudeCodeDriver` from `./claude-code.js`\n62\t   **And** existing factory exports are preserved\n63\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n64\t\n65\t9. **Given** unit tests in `src/lib/agents/__tests__/claude-code-driver.test.ts`\n66\t   **When** `npm run test:unit` is executed\n67\t   **Then** tests cover: dispatch yields StreamEvent sequence from mocked SDK, getLastCost returns cost from last dispatch, getLastCost returns null when no cost reported, healthCheck returns available/authenticated, error classification for RATE_LIMIT/NETWORK/AUTH/TIMEOUT/UNKNOWN, dispatch always yields a final result event even on error, plugins are passed through to SDK options, timeout handling\n68\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n69\t\n70\t10. **Given** `npm run build` is executed\n71\t    **When** the build completes\n72\t    **Then** it succeeds with zero TypeScript errors\n73\t    **And** `npm run test:unit` passes with no regressions in existing test suites\n74\t    <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n75\t\n76\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n77\t\n78\t- [x] Task 1: Create `src/lib/agents/drivers/claude-code.ts` (AC: #1, #4)\n79\t  - [x] Import `query` from `@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk`\n80\t  - [x] Import types: `AgentDriver`, `DispatchOpts`, `DriverHealth`, `DriverCapabilities` from `../types.js`\n81\t  - [x] Import `StreamEvent` types from `../stream-parser.js`\n82\t  - [x] Implement `ClaudeCodeDriver` class with readonly name, defaultModel, capabilities\n83\t  - [x] Implement `healthCheck()` returning `{ available: true, authenticated: true, version: null }`\n84\t\n85\t- [x] Task 2: Implement `dispatch()` method — SDK integration (AC: #2, #3)\n86\t  - [x] Call `query()` with prompt, model, systemPrompt, cwd, permissionMode from `DispatchOpts`\n87\t  - [x] Consume the Agent SDK async generator and map messages to `StreamEvent` objects\n88\t  - [x] Map `content_block_start` (tool_use) to `tool-start` events\n89\t  - [x] Map `content_block_delta` (input_json_delta) to `tool-input` events\n90\t  - [x] Map `content_block_delta` (text_delta) to `text` events\n91\t  - [x] Map `content_block_stop` to `tool-complete` events\n92\t  - [x] Map system `api_retry` to `retry` events\n93\t  - [x] Map `result` to final `result` event with cost_usd from `total_cost_usd`\n94\t  - [x] Store `total_cost_usd` from result message for `getLastCost()`\n95\t  - [x] Always yield exactly one `result` event at the end\n96\t\n97\t- [x] Task 3: Implement error classification (AC: #5)\n98\t  - [x] Extract `classifyError()` as a private method or module function\n99\t  - [x] Map HTTP 429 or \"rate limit\" in message to `RATE_LIMIT`\n100\t  - [x] Map ECONNREFUSED, ETIMEDOUT, ENOTFOUND, ENETUNREACH, ECONNRESET, EPIPE to `NETWORK`\n101\t  - [x] Map HTTP 401/403 or \"unauthorized\"/\"forbidden\" to `AUTH`\n102\t  - [x] Map timeout kill to `TIMEOUT`\n103\t  - [x] Default to `UNKNOWN`\n104\t  - [x] On error, yield a `result` event with error details instead of throwing\n105\t\n106\t- [x] Task 4: Implement plugin and timeout pass-through (AC: #6, #7)\n107\t  - [x] When `opts.plugins` is provided, pass to SDK query options\n108\t  - [x] When `opts.timeout` is provided, implement timeout with `AbortController` or equivalent\n109\t  - [x] On timeout, abort the SDK generator and yield `result` with TIMEOUT classification\n110\t\n111\t- [x] Task 5: Update `src/lib/agents/drivers/index.ts` barrel (AC: #8)\n112\t  - [x] Add `export { ClaudeCodeDriver } from './claude-code.js'`\n113\t  - [x] Preserve existing factory exports\n114\t\n115\t- [x] Task 6: Write unit tests (AC: #9, #10)\n116\t  - [x] Mock `@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk` query function (same pattern as `agent-dispatch.test.ts`)\n117\t  - [x] Test: dispatch yields correct StreamEvent sequence from mocked SDK messages\n118\t  - [x] Test: getLastCost() returns cost from last result message\n119\t  - [x] Test: getLastCost() returns null before any dispatch\n120\t  - [x] Test: getLastCost() returns null when SDK reports no cost\n121\t  - [x] Test: healthCheck() returns `{ available: true, authenticated: true, version: null }`\n122\t  - [x] Test: error classification for RATE_LIMIT (429 status)\n123\t  - [x] Test: error classification for NETWORK (ECONNREFUSED)\n124\t  - [x] Test: error classification for AUTH (401 status)\n125\t  - [x] Test: error classification for TIMEOUT\n126\t  - [x] Test: error classification for UNKNOWN (default)\n127\t  - [x] Test: dispatch always yields a result event even when SDK throws\n128\t  - [x] Test: plugins array passed to SDK options\n129\t  - [x] Test: no plugins passed when opts.plugins is undefined\n130\t  - [x] Verify `npm run build` passes with zero errors\n131\t  - [x] Verify `npm run test:unit` passes with no regressions\n132\t\n133\t## Dev Notes\n134\t\n135\t### Architecture Compliance\n136\t\n137\tThis story implements the **Claude Code Driver Extraction** from `_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-multi-framework.md` (Decision 1: Driver Interface Design, Decision 2: CLI-Wrapping Strategy). Key constraints:\n138\t\n139\t- **ClaudeCodeDriver is in-process** — Unlike Codex/OpenCode which wrap CLIs via `child_process.spawn`, Claude Code uses the Agent SDK `query()` function directly. No process spawning needed.\n140\t- **Must follow the Driver Implementation Pattern** — Same class structure as all other drivers: implements `AgentDriver`, one file, named export, registered externally.\n141\t- **dispatch() returns AsyncIterable<StreamEvent>** — Use `async *dispatch()` generator. Consume the SDK async generator and yield mapped `StreamEvent` objects.\n142\t- **Error handling: yield, don't throw** — On SDK errors, classify and yield a `result` event with error info. The workflow engine expects a clean event stream, not exceptions.\n143\t\n144\t### Existing Code to Refactor From\n145\t\n146\tThe primary source is `src/lib/agent-dispatch.ts`:\n147\t- **`dispatchAgent()`** — Calls `query()`, consumes the async generator, returns `DispatchResult`. The ClaudeCodeDriver will do the same but yield `StreamEvent` instead of collecting into a result object.\n148\t- **`classifyError()`** — Maps errors to `DispatchErrorCode`. Adapt this to produce `ErrorCategory` (the new type has `AUTH` and `TIMEOUT` categories that the old code maps to `SDK_INIT` or `UNKNOWN`).\n149\t- **`NETWORK_CODES`** set — Reuse directly for network error detection.\n150\t- **Error wrapping** — The old code throws `DispatchError`. The new code must yield a `result` event instead. Do not throw from `dispatch()`.\n151\t\n152\t### Critical Mapping: SDK Messages to StreamEvent\n153\t\n154\tThe Agent SDK `query()` yields messages with various structures. Map them as follows:\n155\t\n156\t| SDK Message | StreamEvent |\n157\t|-------------|-------------|\n158\t| `{ type: 'stream_event', event: { type: 'content_block_start', content_block: { type: 'tool_use', name, id } } }` | `{ type: 'tool-start', name, id }` |\n159\t| `{ type: 'stream_event', event: { type: 'content_block_delta', delta: { type: 'input_json_delta', partial_json } } }` | `{ type: 'tool-input', partial: partial_json }` |\n160\t| `{ type: 'stream_event', event: { type: 'content_block_delta', delta: { type: 'text_delta', text } } }` | `{ type: 'text', text }` |\n161\t| `{ type: 'stream_event', event: { type: 'content_block_stop' } }` | `{ type: 'tool-complete' }` |\n162\t| `{ type: 'system', subtype: 'api_retry', attempt, retry_delay_ms }` | `{ type: 'retry', attempt, delay }` |\n163\t| `{ type: 'result', total_cost_usd, session_id }` | `{ type: 'result', cost: total_cost_usd, sessionId: session_id }` |\n164\t\n165\tThis is the same mapping used by `parseStreamLine()` in `stream-parser.ts`, but applied directly to SDK message objects instead of NDJSON lines. Reuse the same logic/patterns but adapt for the SDK's object format.\n166\t\n167\t### What NOT to Do\n168\t\n169\t- Do NOT modify `agent-dispatch.ts` — it stays as-is until story 10-5 replaces callers. Backward compatibility.\n170\t- Do NOT register `ClaudeCodeDriver` in the factory module — registration happens at bootstrap (story 10-5).\n171\t- Do NOT modify `workflow-engine.ts` — integration comes in story 10-5.\n172\t- Do NOT create `codex.ts` or `opencode.ts` — those are stories 12-1 and 12-2.\n173\t- Do NOT modify `stream-parser.ts` — the existing parser is for NDJSON lines; the driver uses SDK objects directly.\n174\t- Do NOT add the driver to any initialization code — no automatic instantiation.\n175\t\n176\t### Dependencies\n177\t\n178\t- **Story 10-1 (done):** `AgentDriver` interface, `DispatchOpts`, `DriverHealth`, `DriverCapabilities`, `ErrorCategory` types in `src/lib/agents/types.ts`\n179\t- **Story 10-2 (done):** Driver factory in `src/lib/agents/drivers/factory.ts` — this story does NOT register the driver, but the factory is available for future stories.\n180\t- **External:** `@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk` — already a project dependency (`query` function).\n181\t\n182\t### Testing Patterns\n183\t\n184\t- Follow existing Vitest patterns in `src/lib/__tests__/agent-dispatch.test.ts`\n185\t- Mock `@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk` using `vi.mock()` with `vi.hoisted()` pattern (same as existing test)\n186\t- Create async generator helpers (`fakeStream()`) to simulate SDK responses\n187\t- Use `beforeEach()` to reset mock state\n188\t- Test error classification by feeding different error shapes and asserting the yielded result event\n189\t- Test the full dispatch flow: mock SDK, call dispatch, collect yielded events, verify sequence\n190\t\n191\t### Implementation Notes\n192\t\n193\t- **Default model:** `'claude-sonnet-4-20250514'` — matches architecture doc Decision 4 driver defaults.\n194\t- **healthCheck()** is trivial for Claude Code — the Agent SDK is an npm dependency, always available if the package installed correctly. Return `{ available: true, authenticated: true, version: null }`. Auth is checked lazily on first API call, not eagerly.\n195\t- **getLastCost()** stores cost from the most recent dispatch only. Initialize to `null`. Update on each dispatch's result message.\n196\t- **Cost field:** Use `total_cost_usd` from the SDK result message. Map to `result.cost` for the `ResultEvent`. Also store for `getLastCost()`.\n197\t- **Plugin pass-through:** The Agent SDK `query()` options may accept plugin configuration. Check SDK types for the correct option shape. If not directly supported, pass via `systemPrompt` appendage or environment variables.\n198\t- **Timeout:** Use `AbortController` with `setTimeout`. Pass the abort signal to the SDK if supported, or manually break the generator consumption loop.\n199\t\n200\t### Project Structure Notes\n201\t\n202\t- New file: `src/lib/agents/drivers/claude-code.ts` — follows the `{driver-name}.ts` naming convention from architecture.\n203\t- Test file: `src/lib/agents/__tests__/claude-code-driver.test.ts` — follows existing pattern of tests in `__tests__/` directory.\n204\t- Barrel update: `src/lib/agents/drivers/index.ts` — add export for new class.\n205\t- No new directories needed — `drivers/` directory exists from story 10-2.\n206\t\n207\t### References\n208\t\n209\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-multi-framework.md — Decision 1: Driver Interface Design]\n210\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-multi-framework.md — Decision 2: CLI-Wrapping Strategy (for in-process variant)]\n211\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-multi-framework.md — Implementation Patterns: Driver Implementation Pattern]\n212\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-multi-framework.md — Implementation Patterns: StreamEvent Production Pattern]\n213\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-multi-framework.md — Implementation Patterns: Error Classification Pattern]\n214\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-multi-framework.md — Story 1.3: Claude Code Driver Extraction]\n215\t- [Source: src/lib/agent-dispatch.ts — existing dispatch logic to refactor from]\n216\t- [Source: src/lib/agents/types.ts — AgentDriver interface (story 10-1)]\n217\t- [Source: src/lib/agents/drivers/factory.ts — driver factory (story 10-2)]\n218\t- [Source: src/lib/agents/stream-parser.ts — StreamEvent types and parseStreamLine pattern]\n219\t- [Source: src/lib/__tests__/agent-dispatch.test.ts — testing patterns for SDK mocking]\n220\t\n221\t## Dev Agent Record\n222\t\n223\t### Agent Model Used\n224\t\n225\tClaude Opus 4.6 (1M context)\n226\t\n227\t### Debug Log References\n228\t\n229\tN/A\n230\t\n231\t### Completion Notes List\n232\t\n233\t- Created `ClaudeCodeDriver` class implementing `AgentDriver` interface with in-process SDK dispatch\n234\t- Implemented full SDK message-to-StreamEvent mapping (tool-start, tool-input, tool-complete, text, retry, result)\n235\t- Implemented `classifyError()` with 5-category classification: RATE_LIMIT, NETWORK, AUTH, TIMEOUT, UNKNOWN\n236\t- Error handling yields result events instead of throwing — clean event stream for workflow engine\n237\t- Plugin pass-through: passes `plugins` array to SDK query options when non-empty\n238\t- Timeout handling via `AbortController` with automatic TIMEOUT classification on abort\n239\t- `getLastCost()` tracks cost from most recent dispatch, resets to null on each new dispatch\n240\t- `healthCheck()` returns static `{ available: true, authenticated: true, version: null }` (in-process dependency)\n241\t- Barrel file updated to re-export `ClaudeCodeDriver`\n242\t- 42 unit tests covering all acceptance criteria — all passing\n243\t- Build succeeds with zero TypeScript errors in new files\n244\t- Full regression suite: 163 test files, 4283 tests, all passing\n245\t\n246\t### Change Log\n247\t\n248\t- 2026-04-03: Story implemented — ClaudeCodeDriver extraction from agent-dispatch.ts patterns\n249\t\n250\t### File List\n251\t\n252\t- src/lib/agents/drivers/claude-code.ts (new)\n253\t- src/lib/agents/drivers/index.ts (modified)\n254\t- src/lib/agents/__tests__/claude-code-driver.test.ts (new)\n255\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01ANtbcVL9VAAWRaokkDe44o","session_id":"ccf790f5-4b27-4b46-b089-256c4e0022f0","uuid":"7304c978-9b01-4aa5-9bbc-6bde20e2485f","timestamp":"2026-04-03T07:10:42.235Z"}
