{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PWWRit16tQswFV3gtpnSgx","type":"tool_result","content":"2080\t7. **Prediction validated.** Session 3 predicted Epic 10 stories would maintain ~$4-5/story. Actual: ~$3.50. Types-heavy work is cheaper.\n2081\t\n2082\t---\n2083\t\n2084\t## 5. What Went Wrong\n2085\t\n2086\t1. **Epic numbering mismatch still causing friction.** create-story phase wasted glob calls because sprint-status IDs don't match epics file IDs. This has been flagged in Sessions 3 and 4 — still not fixed.\n2087\t2. **Planning artifacts path assumption baked into subagents.** Subagents expect files at `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/` but planning docs live at `_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/`. Every create-story phase burns 2-3 extra tool calls on this.\n2088\t3. **AGENTS.md doc-gate still fires.** `codeharness verify` exits 1 every time due to stale AGENTS.md. At this point it's noise, not signal.\n2089\t4. **`codeharness stats` still broken for non-ralph sessions.** Same issue as Sessions 1-3. Cost analysis relies on manual aggregation from session issues log.\n2090\t5. **Overlapping test runs in verification.** `npm test` and `npx vitest run --reporter=verbose` are redundant — both run the same test suite. One call wasted.\n2091\t\n2092\t---\n2093\t\n2094\t## 6. Lessons Learned\n2095\t\n2096\t### Patterns to Repeat\n2097\t\n2098\t- **Small, well-scoped stories with pure-logic modules yield fast, cheap, bug-free cycles.** Story 10-2 had clear ACs, no I/O dependencies, and a well-known pattern. This is the ideal unit of work for autonomous execution.\n2099\t- **Code review input validation catches MEDIUM bugs consistently.** `null`/empty-string guards were missing — these are the kind of bugs that cause confusing runtime errors weeks later.\n2100\t- **Session issues log as the single source of truth for subagent metrics** continues to work. No need for `codeharness stats` if subagents self-report.\n2101\t\n2102\t### Patterns to Avoid\n2103\t\n2104\t- **Running overlapping test commands in verification phase.** `npm test` and `npx vitest run --reporter=verbose` are the same suite. Pick one.\n2105\t- **Leaving path assumptions hardcoded in subagent prompts.** The planning-artifacts vs implementation-artifacts path mismatch wastes tool calls every session.\n2106\t\n2107\t---\n2108\t\n2109\t## 7. Action Items\n2110\t\n2111\t### From Prior Sessions (status update)\n2112\t\n2113\t| # | Action | Priority | Status |\n2114\t|---|--------|----------|--------|\n2115\t| 1 | ~~Complete code-review and verify for story 5-1~~ | ~~HIGH~~ | DONE (Session 2) |\n2116\t| 2 | Fix `codeharness verify` to work without pre-set harness state flags | MEDIUM | Open |\n2117\t| 3 | Update `src/lib/AGENTS.md` — still missing: agent-dispatch, agent-resolver, session-manager, trace-id, factory | MEDIUM | Open (grew by 1) |\n2118\t| 4 | Fix `codeharness stats --save` to work for non-ralph sessions | LOW | Open |\n2119\t| 5 | Sync `ralph/.state-snapshot.json` with `sprint-state.json` | LOW | Open |\n2120\t| 6 | Fix pre-existing TS errors in `src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts` | LOW | Open |\n2121\t| 7 | Address deferred LOW issues from code reviews | LOW | Open |\n2122\t| 8 | Add integration test for actual YAML parsing in workflow-engine | LOW | Open |\n2123\t\n2124\t### New This Session\n2125\t\n2126\t| # | Action | Priority | Owner |\n2127\t|---|--------|----------|-------|\n2128\t| 9 | Fix epic numbering mismatch between sprint-status (10-2) and epics file (Epic 1 Story 1.2) | MEDIUM | Next sprint planning |\n2129\t| 10 | Update subagent create-story prompts to check `planning-artifacts/` as fallback path | MEDIUM | Backlog |\n2130\t| 11 | Deduplicate `createMockDriver` helper across test files | LOW | Backlog |\n2131\t| 12 | Add runtime interface validation to `registerDriver()` | LOW | Backlog |\n2132\t| 13 | Eliminate redundant test runs in verification phase (pick `npm test` OR `vitest --reporter=verbose`, not both) | LOW | Backlog |\n2133\t\n2134\t### Next Story\n2135\t\n2136\tStory **10-3-claude-code-driver-extraction** is next in the sprint backlog. This will be more complex than 10-2 — it involves extracting the existing Claude Code spawning logic into the new AgentDriver interface, which touches runtime I/O and process management.\n2137\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01RQCtb27pZs291zmdmd8MaZ","session_id":"ccf790f5-4b27-4b46-b089-256c4e0022f0","uuid":"33371ac3-e931-437c-8681-fff5211e89df","timestamp":"2026-04-03T07:15:29.191Z"}
